7 administrative regulations of the department promulgated pursuant to KRS
8 441.055;
9 (b) The construction results in a new facility with:
10 1. A minimum capacity of one hundred fifty (150) prisoner beds, except as
11 provided in subsection (5) of this section; or
12 2. If a larger facility is needed, more than one hundred fifty (150) prisoner
13 beds in fifty (50) bed increments; and
14 (c) Construction of the local correctional facility is approved by the construction
15 authority.
16 (2) Final authority for approval of plans for the construction of a local correctional
17 facility, or an addition to a local correctional facility shall rest with the construction
18 authority.
19 (3) The department shall pay for the architectural plans and engineering services
20 associated with any new local correctional facility approved by the construction
21 authority.
22 (4) The department may promulgate administrative regulations to create a fee schedule
23 for architectural plans and engineering services required for the construction of
24 local correctional facilities. A sample fee schedule for architectural plans and
25 engineering services may be developed by a committee consisting of department
26 personnel, architects, and construction managers.
